eight="2304" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/15f92030-020e-11ee-b9ee-88a9790bba0a" width="4096"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2304" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/15f92030-020e-11ee-b9ee-88a9790bba0a" width="4096"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Nintendo]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A promo photo for Nintendo's Everybody 1-2 Switch game. It shows a person with a horse mask on at the center, surrounded by people with their hands curled into a riding pose in front of them at the left side. At their right side, a bunch of people are posing with their hands above their heads while holding their phone.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Everybody 1-2 Switch]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Fitbit users can log in with their Google accounts starting on June 6th]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>我们知道<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/fitbit-google-accounts-integration-084831995.html">它的到来已经</a>有一段时间了，但现在谷歌已经确定了何时开始将 Fitbit 用户转换为谷歌登录。 6 月 6 日，这家科技巨头将为 Fitbit 用户推出使用 Google 凭据登录帐户的选项。在宣布以 21 亿美元收购这家可穿戴设备制造商后即将发生的变化时，该公司表示，当登录支持到来时，人们可以选择将 Fitbit 设备转移到他们的谷歌账户。用户将有机会在移动时调整他们的数据，并可以选择从 Fitbit 应用程序或他们的 Google 设置页面管理他们的信息。</p><p>虽然使用 Google 登录 Fitbit 目前只是一种选择，但很快用户将别无选择。该公司计划在今年某个时候要求使用谷歌登录来注册一个新的 Fitbit 账户并激活新的运动设备和智能手表。然后到 2025 年，它将完全终止对 Fitbit 账户的支持。那些计划坚持使用 Fitbit 品牌的人只需要把他们的设备链接到他们的谷歌账户就可以了。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>这家科技巨头将整合展示为用户“管理所有 [他们] 连接的应用程序和配对设备”的简便方法。但它知道有些人会担心他们信息的隐私，因此它 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://blog.google/products/fitbit/google-accounts-for-fitbit/">之前表示</a>不会将 Fitbit 用户的健康数据用于 Google Ads。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/fitbit-users-can-log-in-with-their-google-accounts-starting-on-june-6th-173329923.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/fitbit-users-can-log-in-with-their-google-accounts-starting-on-june-6th-173329923.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f61f763d-6ea8-44f4-ba70-ec4f1c86e803</guid><dc:creator>玛丽拉月亮</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sat, 03 Jun 2023 17:33:29 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685796774</ingested><modified> 2023-06-03T12:52:57+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="2403" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-01/106e1650-5673-11eb-baf3-0cc506027861" width="3795"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2403" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-01/106e1650-5673-11eb-baf3-0cc506027861" width="3795"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Anadolu Agency via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[BRUSSELS, BELGIUM - AUGUST 04: Logo of Google is displayed on a smartphone as logo of fitbit is seen in Brussels, Belgium on August 04, 2020. (Photo by Dursun Aydemir/Anadolu Agency via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[EU continue to investigate Google on purchasing Fitbit]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft is killing the standalone Cortana app for Windows in late 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>显然， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-windows-copilot-ai-panos-panay-interview-150044298.html">Windows Copilot 的推出</a>标志着 Cortana 在微软桌面操作系统上的终结。在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.windowscentral.com/software-apps/windows-11/microsoft-is-killing-cortana-on-windows-11-and-windows-10-later-this-year"><em>Windows Central</em></a>最先发现的一份新<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Microsoft;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=67071605-d4df-494e-8d9c-c9c236b8bb38&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Microsoft&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYhabk4PVs7l6PKmiObU7YjB0-yk3C7gYriX4mSZFsmK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Ftopic%2Fend-of-support-for-cortana-in-windows-d025b39f-ee5b-4836-a954-0ab646ee1efa" class="rapid-with-clickid">支持文件</a>中，这家科技巨头宣布将在 2023 年底停止支持适用于 Windows 的独立 Cortana 应用程序。微软早在 2014 年就<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2014-06-04-cortana-microsoft-windows-phone.html">推出了</a>Cortana 作为 Windows 移动设备的语音助手。是该公司对苹果 Siri 的回应，它甚至早于亚马逊的 Alexa，但它从未完全达到他们的认可度和流行度。</p><p>一年来，微软缩减了语音助手的计划，直到 2021 年<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cortana-shutdown-harman-kardon-invoke-ios-android-191700426.html">停止使用</a>其 Android 和 iOS 应用程序。该公司甚至将其从合作伙伴制造商的设备中移除，例如智能扬声器。尤其是对于 Windows，微软改变了其内置数字助理的地位，并将<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-06-28-microsoft-cortana-separate-app.html">其拆分</a>为自己的计算机应用程序。这是我们将在今年年底告别的应用程序。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>微软在公告中指出，用户仍然可以使用“Windows 和 Edge 中强大的生产力功能，这些功能增强了 AI 功能”。它特别提到了现在由 OpenAI 的 GPT-4 技术提供支持的新 Bing。微软在 3 月份推出了<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-365-copilot-uses-ai-to-automate-everyday-tasks-in-multiple-apps-151133434.html">Microsoft 365 Copilot</a>工具，该工具可以使用基于文本的提示在 Office 应用程序中创建内容。</p><p>然后在 5 月下旬，该公司在其 Build 开发者大会上透露，通过在平台的侧边栏中放置一个 Copilot 工具，它正在使 AI 成为 Windows 11 的一个深度集成部分。用户可以要求它在操作系统中执行任务，例如更改计算机背景，甚至编辑照片和总结文档，而无需启动应用程序或搜索特定设置。很可能很少有人会想念 Cortana。那些确实使用助手的人可以过渡到使用 Copilot，从本月开始，它将作为 Windows 11 的预览版提供。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-is-killing-the-standalone-cortana-app-for-windows-in-late-2023-142437631.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-is-killing-the-standalone-cortana-app-for-windows-in-late-2023-142437631.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a3b2f5ec-59f4-49db-ab26-70c874ada6cf</guid><dc:creator>玛丽拉月亮</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Sat, 03 Jun 2023 14:24:37 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1685794854</ingested><modified> 2023-06-03T12:20:58+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="5464" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/f8110260-f969-11ed-be59-bafd486fa5b7" width="8192"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:cred